reviews.review_text: Seattle's Shinning Star This recording has splices of the aud source for a couple songs and it is rough and the levels are not as balanced as they could be. Im particularly a fan of the playin here though. Definately a representative of the way they jammed it out in this time period.

Nice AUD from the 1973 Summer The other reviewer is actually speaking about the SBD copy of this show, not this AUD.  This recording was done by the same taper of 6/22/73, and while it isn't quite as glorious as that tape, it is a wonderful recording none-the-less.  It gets you right in the pocket of a great audience recording of a 1973 show.  Thow Other One is outstanding.

This is a sound.  The Playing has some great moments of several instruments dancing solos around each other. It's incredible, unique, and exquisite. Nearly every playing from this period is though. This one's a tad shorter than usual, but represents out of this world ensemble playing in a genre that will never be classified. Space-Jazz-Rock? 

The sound here is exactly what a show from '73 should be...Awesome! 

this aud rocks.
